<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="603" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">694.001/6–2251: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the United States Political Adviser to <gloss target="#t_SCAP1">SCAP</gloss>
                                </hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sebald</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d603fn1">Telegram
                                    drafted by Mr. Fearey and cleared by U. Alexis Johnson.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-22T19:00:00-04:00">June
                                        22, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Topad1">Topad</gloss> 1803. For Allison. Emb
                                London has just advised “Cabinet yesterday approved revised treaty
                                draft subj only to reservation on shipbuilding.” States <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> asking Glutton approach you
                                on your arrival Jap re “suggested unilateral undertaking by Jap Govt
                                voluntarily to limit shipbuilding.”<note n="2" xml:id="d603fn2">The
                                    quotation is from telegram 6747 from London, June 22. The
                                    sentence following the section quoted above follows: “Not only
                                    Brit shipbuilders but also ship operators and seamen’s unions
                                    extremely vocal on question Jap maritime competition.”
                                    (694.001/6–2251)</note> References shipbuilding puzzling but
                                will presumably be clarified by Glutton.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>